main event: A civilian witness observed one to two round, colored lights moving slowly over Orlando, Florida on May 6, 1966.
interesting points: The lights changed colors, moving from red to green to blue and then all white.
The lights made erratic movements, stopping, reversing direction, and leveling off.
The witness watched the objects for 25-42 minutes.
The report includes weather data and details on the witness's background.
The case was deemed insufficient for evaluation due to lack of substantial facts.
